Medog County, located in the southeastern region of Xizang , belongs to one significant biodiversity hotspots—the Indo-Burma hotspots (
;
). Thanks to its distinctive bio-geography, varied topography, and an impressive altitudinal range that spans 7,500 meters within a mere 40 kilometers, the southeastern area of Xizang proudly stands as a biodiversity hotspot with exceptionally rich ecological diversity (
;
).
W . lianhua
sp. nov.
is the first record of Gryllacrididae for Xizang . Southeastern region including Medog is highly worthwhile for taxonomists to delve deeper, enabling a better understanding of its ecological and species diversity through further exploration, ultimately contributing to enhanced conservation efforts.
